    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-04T05:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-04T05:35:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/711: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-04T14:00:00+03:25"
                            >January 4, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. My 435, December 13.<note n="93" xml:id="d461fn93">
                        <ref target="frus1942v04#pg_315">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1942, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 315</ref>.</note> Prime Minister<note
                        n="94" xml:id="d461fn94">Ahmad Qavam.</note> yesterday expressed to me his
                    concern over fact that Soviet Government has not yet given approval for the
                    taking over by Americans of operation of southern section of Trans-Iranian
                    Railway. Soviet consent is considered to be essential under the terms of the
                    Tripartite Pact.<note n="95" xml:id="d461fn95">Anglo-Soviet-Iranian treaty of
                        alliance, signed at Tehran, January 29, 1942; for text, see Department of
                        State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 21, 1942, p. 249, or British
                        Cmd. 6335, Persia No. 1 (1942).</note> Soviet Ambassador<note n="96"
                        xml:id="d461fn96">A. A. Smirnov.</note> informs me he has taken matter up
                    with his Government but has received no reply.</p>
                <p>Prime Minister in view of the importance and urgency of matter has urged me to
                    request Department’s assistance in obtaining Soviet consent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
